"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1475840 - Don't fail browser_preferences_usage.js because browser.startup.record is only accessed on startup. r=florian\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4327", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/performance/browser_preferences_usage.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4e42a6a201f067a107d0bc0e28508dc2585be87f", "parents": ["7edf18c31ee0e0f598cfd2ae9371ba7c3161afcc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henri Sivonen \u003chsivonen@hsivonen.fi\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1484990 - Use BulkWrite instead of write past length via BeginWriting() in XHR. r=baku\n\nThe old code assumes that it's OK to use nsAString::BeginWriting() to write\npast the string's logical length if the string has enough capacity. This is\nbogus, because the string doesn't know of data written past its logical\nlength.\n\nThe BulkWrite API has been created precisely for this purpose and allows\norderly capacity-aware low-level writes to the string.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: BYQHl8Z9Fbd\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D3886", "files": ["dom/xhr/XMLHttpRequestMainThread.cpp", "dom/xhr/XMLHttpRequestMainThread.h", "dom/xhr/XMLHttpRequestString.cpp", "dom/xhr/XMLHttpRequestString.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "510decfb443d585f9913e12227764fecaad5ea8d", "parents": ["4e42a6a201f067a107d0bc0e28508dc2585be87f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johan Lorenzo \u003cjlorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1484932 - Update GeckoView maven group id: org.mozilla.geckoview r=sebastian,jchen\n\nUpdate GeckoView maven group id: org.mozilla.geckoview\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4344", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/build.gradle", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/beetmover_geckoview.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "75b8ac536f30108bcefb6ffa139a1b57bc43f878", "parents": ["510decfb443d585f9913e12227764fecaad5ea8d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henri Sivonen \u003chsivonen@hsivonen.fi\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1485943 - Avoid writing past the logical length of a string in AlternateServices.cpp. r=dragana\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4xPYaAbGaEI\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4512", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http/AlternateServices.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "79ff858fea6bdff2ae0d7d1fa8c7fd98c0895f0f", "parents": ["75b8ac536f30108bcefb6ffa139a1b57bc43f878"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Razvan Caliman \u003crcaliman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1486409 - Guard against a font property value of zero. Catch NaN and Infinity in unit conversion. r=gl\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4326", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/fonts/components/FontEditor.js", "devtools/client/inspector/fonts/components/FontPropertyValue.js", "devtools/client/inspector/fonts/fonts.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f10df314fc4df9312555af4cc0c6fd7bb32a3b76", "parents": ["79ff858fea6bdff2ae0d7d1fa8c7fd98c0895f0f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreea Pavel \u003capavel@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 510decfb443d (bug 1484990) for breaking many test suites e.g. Wr on a CLOSED TREE", "files": ["dom/xhr/XMLHttpRequestMainThread.cpp", "dom/xhr/XMLHttpRequestMainThread.h", "dom/xhr/XMLHttpRequestString.cpp", "dom/xhr/XMLHttpRequestString.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "618546b5d4416f83f18aa64f556bfa7584bb7be7", "parents": ["f10df314fc4df9312555af4cc0c6fd7bb32a3b76"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Graham \u003cjames@hoppipolla.co.uk\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1485668 - Fix reftest chain comparisons in marionette reftest implementation, r=ato\n\nWe were previously using the original test url as the lhs for each\ncomparison after the top level, rather than the previous rhs url as\nexpected.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4081", "files": ["testing/marionette/reftest.js", "testing/web-platform/meta/MANIFEST.json", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-text/astral-bidi/adlam-anti-ref.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-text/astral-bidi/cypriot-anti-ref.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/infrastructure/reftest/reftest_match.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/tests/infrastructure/reftest/reftest_and_mismatch.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/infrastructure/reftest/reftest_and_mismatch_0.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/infrastructure/reftest/reftest_and_mismatch_1.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0cd882a506cfa9c7489160d06437361430e0aa65", "parents": ["618546b5d4416f83f18aa64f556bfa7584bb7be7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johan Lorenzo \u003cjlorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1483521 - PushAPK shouldn't depend on single-locale android r=Callek\n\nPushAPK shouldn't depend on single-locale android\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D3512", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/push-apk/kind.yml", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/push_apk.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "abdb08a0a1d1d65d5c23a77b97adcbab10debf75", "parents": ["0cd882a506cfa9c7489160d06437361430e0aa65"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Margareta Eliza Balazs \u003cebalazs@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge mozilla-central to autoland. a=merge CLOSED TREE", "files": ["browser/config/mozconfigs/linux64/opt-static-analysis-clang", "gfx/ycbcr/QuellGccWarnings.patch", "gfx/ycbcr/TypeFromSize.patch", "gfx/ycbcr/clang-cl-workaround.patch", "gfx/ycbcr/convert.patch", "gfx/ycbcr/update.sh", "gfx/ycbcr/win64.patch", "layout/xul/crashtests/237787-1.xul", "testing/mozharness/configs/builds/releng_sub_linux_configs/64_fuzzing_ccov.py", "testing/mozharness/configs/b