cf39577a0aae49b496dc79a1c3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jeff Muizelaar \u003cjmuizelaar@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1487588. Update webrender to commit 6415faa7f6acd412d4cc6b745cf802204690611c", "files": ["gfx/webrender/src/display_list_flattener.rs", "gfx/webrender/src/render_backend.rs", "gfx/webrender/src/scene_builder.rs", "gfx/webrender_api/src/api.rs", "gfx/webrender_bindings/revision.txt", "gfx/wrench/src/reftest.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d675059c7ee6099c15818f5d08b46610c1c13869", "parents": ["57e362dbff454de4ae08dbeef0bb72d7cbf37e0b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jeff Muizelaar \u003cjmuizelaar@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1487588. Increase fuzz on 3d transform test a bit to avoid orange.", "files": ["layout/reftests/transform-3d/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "930e12a89a4371a2b62c9fef59d6be4eed21914e", "parents": ["d675059c7ee6099c15818f5d08b46610c1c13869"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gurzau Raul \u003crgurzau@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge mozilla-central to inbound.  a=merge CLOSED TREE", "files": ["other-licenses/7zstub/src/CPP/7zip/Bundles/SFXSetup/SfxSetup.cpp", "other-licenses/7zstub/src/CPP/7zip/Bundles/SFXSetup/resource.h", "other-licenses/7zstub/src/CPP/7zip/Bundles/SFXSetup/resource.rc", "other-licenses/7zstub/src/CPP/7zip/UI/FileManager/ProgressDialog.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "19f0b4b0fada080b2f2cbdc6a554aba739b7739a", "parents": ["930e12a89a4371a2b62c9fef59d6be4eed21914e", "02f33375bc170cc26faeb9284f11d74f653565ea"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1487460 - Add gcc dependency for linux opt builds to make beta happy. r=dmajor\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4724\n", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/build/linux.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e9d7d713913290df6f3e1c4a23677b5a96194e81", "parents": ["19f0b4b0fada080b2f2cbdc6a554aba739b7739a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1422583 - [marionette] Reset double click tracker when releasing actions. r=ato\n\nGiven that all internal states for the virtual devices are getting\ncleared when releasing actions, also the timer for double click\nevent detection has to be canceled.", "files": ["testing/marionette/listener.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b306b75c312ae63620710fbdb2fd05201297c28f", "parents": ["e9d7d713913290df6f3e1c4a23677b5a96194e81"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1422583 - [wdspec] Add action tests for double click state when releasing action chain. r=ato\n\nThe click status of a mouse action has to be carried forward\nto the next \"Perform Actions\" call if the action sequence\nhasn't been reset before.", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/MANIFEST.json", "testing/web-platform/tests/webdriver/tests/actions/sequence.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3ec600e74178311e39182f2de58dda01534cdb5b", "parents": ["b306b75c312ae63620710fbdb2fd05201297c28f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Cameron McCormack \u003ccam@mcc.id.au\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1487582 - Use an Atom to represent Direction values in pseudo-classes. r=xidorn\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4730", "files": ["servo/components/style/gecko/selector_parser.rs", "servo/components/style/gecko/wrapper.rs", "servo/components/style/invalidation/element/element_wrapper.rs", "servo/components/style/invalidation/element/invalidation_map.rs", "servo/components/style/selector_parser.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "60f2fed43451da188478d6a29672c69776731e3e", "parents": ["3ec600e74178311e39182f2de58dda01534cdb5b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicholas Nethercote \u003cnnethercote@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1486486 - Remove bogus link override code in about:memory. r=bz\n\nIt's throwing because things like `about:memory#end0` aren't valid selectors.", "files": ["toolkit/components/aboutmemory/content/aboutMemory.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d929a08b7cce07e1a902403cd71328b4a8ac448a", "parents": ["60f2fed43451da188478d6a29672c69776731e3e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicholas Nethercote \u003cnnethercote@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1486358 - Mark GetTransactionAtIndex() as NS_IMETHODIMP. r=me\n\nBecause of one this bug's earlier commits made it an XPIDL method.", "files": ["docshell/shistory/nsSHistory.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bea6259e3a50b06d4398559d6eb530e1973981b8", "parents": ["d929a08b7cce07e1a902403cd71328b4a8ac448a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicholas Nethercote \u003cnnethercote@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1487541 - Keep mRequestedIndex in bounds in PurgeHistory(). r=me", "files": ["docshell/shistory/nsSHistory.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "57f23dc56b70bfb36ef223a87cce2ebc4645a443", "parents": ["bea6259e3a50b06d4398559d6eb530e1973981b8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Margareta Eliza Balazs \u003cebalazs@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 96b5a88ac004 (bug 1486824) for causing frequent failures e.g: browser/components/privatebrowsing/test/browser/browser_privatebrowsing_about.js a=backout", "files": ["accessible/tests/browser/events/browser_test_textcaret.js", "browser/base/content/browser-captivePortal.js", "browser/base/content/browser.js", "browser/base/content/test/captivePortal/head.js", "browser/base/content/test/forms/browser_selectpopup.js", "browser/base/content/test/plugins/browser_private_clicktoplay.js", "browser/base/content/test/sidebar/browser_sidebar_adopt.js", "browser/components/customizableui/test/browser_editcontrols_update.js", "browser/components/customizableui/test/browser_sidebar_toggle.js", "browser/components/extensions/test/browser/browser_ext_sidebarAction_windows.js", "browser/components/privatebrowsing/test/browser/browser_privatebrowsing_about.js", "browser/components/sessionstore/test/browser_394759_perwindowpb.js", "dom/tests/browser/browser_bug1236512.js", "testing/mochitest/BrowserTestUtils/BrowserTestUtils.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "63d2134f95878cabfb89c7849a1baad2ef139fd0", "parents": ["02f33375bc170cc26faeb9284f11d74f653565ea"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Margareta Eliza Balazs \u003cebalazs@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge autoland to mozilla-central. a=merge", "files": [], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "bc7c9760b7d1db79ff9eaefbe17b871a6a50ea65", "parents": ["63d2134f95878cabfb89c7849a1baad2ef139fd0", "b073a55c2be73fc6e5ba1a0f2bcef7c61d4d68ef"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Margareta Eliza Balazs \u003cebalazs@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge inbound to mozilla-central.  a=merge", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-transforms/transform3d-preserve3d-011.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "ea869706644d3b2354b2438c77671d6e43df5e99", "parents": ["bc7c9760b7d1db79ff9eaefbe17b871a6a50ea65", "57f23dc56b70bfb36ef223a87cce2ebc4645a443"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Margareta Eliza Balazs \u003cebalazs@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge mozilla-central to autoland. a=merge CLOSED TREE", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.js", "browser/base/content/test/forms/browser_selectpopup.js", "browser/components/customizableui/test/browser_editcontrols_update.js", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-transforms/transform3d-preserve3d-011.html.ini", "toolkit/components/aboutmemory/content/aboutMemory.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "23ac0383d77ecfddb53f46744667f2c7472aaf66", "parents": ["9ed022a889da3f522a18817ea9588e729a100717", "ea869706644d3b2354b2438c77671d6e43df5e99"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Paolo Amadini \u003cpaolo.mozmail@amadzone.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1487496 - Dropdown marker is blurred when disabled. r=dao\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4750", "files": ["toolkit/themes/shared/in-content/common.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3050ceae2cbb384fb0535e3c7c2425805a9dc085", "parents": ["23ac0383d77ecfddb53f46744667f2c7472aaf66"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daniel Stenberg \u003cdaniel@haxx.se\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1487432 - make LOAD_DISABLE_TRR enforce a different hashkey r=valentin\n\nso that such requests don't inadvertently reuse connections done that\nmight have used TRR.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2bO4VCGSgOO\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4693", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpChannel.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpConnectionInfo.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpConnectionInfo.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6550838c80462ef561b14bb5632cf784532ef725", "parents": ["3050ceae2cbb384fb0535e3c7c2425805a9dc085"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Martin Stransky \u003cstransky@redhat.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1477268 - Use window manager decorations instead of CSD mode on Unity, r=jhorak\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4746", "files": ["widget/gtk/nsWindow.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "da1a71bb37fd6465cba22f83b861358b029a0e35", "parents": ["6550838c80462ef561b14bb5632cf784532ef725"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Vlad Baicu \u003cvlad.baicu@softvision.ro\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1479314 - Prevent media control notification flashing. r=jchen\n\nInstead of stopping the foreground service whenever ACTION_PAUSE was triggered,\nI created a new event where we notify the service to clear its foreground state.\nCleared usages of the NotificationManager and the onGoing attribute of the\nMediaNotification because they are redundant. As of Android 4.3 a service in the\nforeground state will always force the notification to be persistent and callling\nstopForeground(false) will clear the onGoing flag while maintaining the notification.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4567", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/media/GeckoMediaControlAgent.java", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/media/MediaControlService.java", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/media/MediaNotification.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0851a63dc3bb203836395607d12fdacd1337e70e", "parents": ["da1a71bb37fd6465cba22f83b861358b029a0e35"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrei Lazar \u003candrei.a.lazar@softvision.ro\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1485719 (New_Tab_Deeplink) Deeplink to open new tab experience in app r=jchen\n\nAdded an extra check for package name for a better user experience, because the push notifications with \"about\" protocol\nin the URL message were still firing the chooser dialog.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4578", "files": ["mobile/android/thirdparty/com/leanplum/messagetemplates/OpenURL.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "725ae58953d8790a667f45f6d4800efa720a7538", "parents": ["0851a63dc3bb203836395607d12fdacd1337e70e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Martin Stransky \u003cstransky@redhat.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1485969 - Enable titlebar rendering on Enlightenment desktop, r=jhorak\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4755", "files": ["widget/gtk/nsWindow.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cd72be2928eae2b1bf1952a05fa475c1668cc0f4", "parents": ["725ae58953d8790a667f45f6d4800efa720a7538"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1487603 - Update llvm-dsymutil to 7rc2. r=dmajor,firefox-build-system-reviewers\n\nLast time it was updated is bug 1436208, and the crashes we patched it\nfor back then has been fixed upstream a few months later.\n\nFor some reason, they renamed the executable from llvm-dsymutil to\ndsymutil.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4741", "files": ["build/macosx/cross-mozconfig.common", "taskcluster/scripts/misc/build-llvm-dsymutil.sh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a9655235ed2c295c1559e0f09bd0566ea441e0d8", "parents": ["cd72be2928eae2b1bf1952a05fa475c1668cc0f4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dimi Lee \u003cdlee@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1476118 - Add .oxt to the list of executable extensions in download protection. r=francois\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4341", "files": ["toolkit/components/reputationservice/ApplicationReputation.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "953cfa4e5a85bc7126c1500eb537765e9b785aaa", "parents": ["a9655235ed2c295c1559e0f09bd0566ea441e0d8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Liang-Heng Chen \u003cxeonchen@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1485400 - Part 0: separate blocked tracker counter; r=smaug\n\nseparate tracker counter API\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4490", "files": ["dom/base/nsIDocument.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9370432b26adcd6399e586190a47d4c8a8cdc56d", "parents": ["953cfa4e5a85bc7126c1500eb537765e9b785aaa"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Liang-Heng Chen \u003cxeonchen@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1485400 - Part 1: fix tracker found/blocked counter; r=mayhemer\n\nmake counter increased when trackers are found\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4068", "files": ["netwerk/base/nsChannelClassifier.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpBaseChannel.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpChannelChild.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpChannel.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c476aa79a8ca991dc8ea1e5c2eab98e442dad406", "parents": ["9370432b26adcd6399e586190a47d4c8a8cdc56d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Henning \u003cjh+bugzilla@buttercookie.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1484001 - Avoid ending up with a null mRuntime after restoring state in GeckoView. r=snorp\n\nIf we don't have a saved session, we do nothing. If somebody called setSession\nbeforehand, we continue using that session, otherwise we create a fallback\nsession in onAttachedToWindow().\n\nIf we have a saved session and nobody called setSession, we use the saved\nsession. If the saved session was closed and doesn't have a runtime, we use the\ndefault runtime as a fallback.\n\nIf we have both a saved session and somebody already called setSession, we\ntransfer what can be transferred from the saved session, unless the saved\nsession is closed and the session from setSession is open.\nIf the saved session was open, we use its runtime as well going forward (since\ntransferring the state from an open session transfers the window and the runtime\nas well), otherwise we keep the old mRuntime.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4711", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/GeckoView.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "34d7cf7fa7eb1c51c6e7f2b4cbf3e5da20ba36d8", "parents": ["c476aa79a8ca991dc8ea1e5c2eab98e442dad406"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Coroiu Cristina \u003cccoroiu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out 2 changesets (bug 1485400) for build bustage at build/src/netwerk/base/nsChannelClassifier.cpp on a CLOSED TREE\n\nBacked out changeset c476aa79a8ca (bug 1485400)\nBacked out changeset 9370432b26ad (bug 1485400)", "files": ["dom/base/nsIDocument.h", "netwerk/base/nsChannelClassifier.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpBaseChannel.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpChannelChild.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpChannel.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8d89bfeb0b2f480a638e83a7d0178039033438f1", "parents": ["34d7cf7fa7eb1c51c6e7f2b4cbf3e5da20ba36d8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Halberstadt \u003cahalberstadt@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1487425 - [mozlint] Fix regression where 'roll' returns dict instead of ResultSummary when no files linted, r=Gijs\n\nThis is a regression from bug 1460856.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4759", "files": ["python/mozlint/mozlint/roller.py", "python/mozlint/test/test_roller.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "56d916d0bfb187bfffc634ea8b10d4f984cc7ed4", "parents": ["8d89bfeb0b2f480a638e83a7d0178039033438f1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Liang-Heng Chen \u003cxeonchen@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1485400 - Part 0: separate blocked tracker counter; r=smaug\n\nseparate tracker counter API\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4490", "files": ["dom/base/nsIDocument.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3897c3140df06d516c3fd8dbf20879b2da8b4caa", "parents": ["56d916d0bfb187bfffc634ea8b10d4f984cc7ed4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Liang-Heng Chen \u003cxeonchen@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1485400 - Part 1: fix tracker found/blocked counter; r=mayhemer\n\nmake counter increased when trackers are found\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4068", "files": ["netwerk/base/nsChannelClassifier.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpBaseChannel.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpChannelChild.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpChannel.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "70042a7ea627ab1c6e299e6790f6c7529f6bdb69", "parents": ["3897c3140df06d516c3fd8dbf20879b2da8b4caa"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Cameron McCormack \u003ccam@mcc.id.au\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1487598 - Use an Atom to store pseudo-class string arguments. r=xidorn\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4740", "files": ["servo/components/style/gecko/selector_parser.rs", "servo/components/style/gecko/wrapper.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c2018c83e3fdc708dbb6629a4360226d34f3f3af", "parents": ["57f23dc56b70bfb36ef223a87cce2ebc4645a443"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Marcos C\u00e1ceres \u003cmarcos@marcosc.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1484864 - Intermittent tier 2 test-verify dom/payments/test/browser_payment_in_different_tabs.js r=edenchuang", "files": ["dom/payments/test/browser_payment_in_different_tabs.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "40b26d4f1ff31207366c019866c1d3da7c604dc9", "parents": ["c2018c83e3fdc708dbb6629a4360226d34f3f3af"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Makoto Kato \u003cm_kato@ga2.so-net.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1487305 - Make HTMLEditor::IsInLink as static method. r=masayuki\n\nSummary:\nNow HTMLEditor::IsInLink returns boolean and nsINode if returning true.\n\nI would like to return Element instead of boolean for reducing refcounting\nand QI like HTMLEditRules::IsInListItem.\n\nReviewers: masayuki\n\nTags: #secure-revision\n\nBug #: 1487305\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4640", "files": ["editor/libeditor/HTMLEditRules.cpp", "editor/libeditor/HTMLEditor.h", "editor/libeditor/HTMLEditorDataTransfer.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "78b5292850ee57667b3b7ed6d410c8a8ff258145", "parents": ["40b26d4f1ff31207366c019866c1d3da7c604dc9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ehsan Akhgari \u003cehsan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1487178 - Ensure that the Firefox configuration is up to date for the Content Blocking project; r=johannh", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "modules/libpref/init/StaticPrefList.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "07abec90d85cb065f17ddb8f75adcc24be5f5f1f", "parents": ["78b5292850ee57667b3b7ed6d410c8a8ff258145"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1487330 - Make mozconfig.{asan,lto,tsan} use mozconfig.linux. r=froydnj\n\nThose mozconfigs do things in common that are already in\nmozconfig.linux. Let's just use that.\n\nThis will make the build have the binutils toolchain in PATH rather than\npassing it to CC/CXX, which is better because it also makes the build\nuse tools such as ar, ranlib, objcopy from the binutils toolchain,\nrather than the old system ones.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4649\n", "files": ["build/unix/mozconfig.asan", "build/unix/mozconfig.lto", "build/unix/mozconfig.tsan"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3fde5ca866c7a6bc71b06fde4ddacf4137823422", "parents": ["07abec90d85cb065f17ddb8f75adcc24be5f5f1f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Margareta Eliza Balazs \u003cebalazs@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge mozilla-central to inbound.  a=merge CLOSED TREE", "files": [], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "2b7a5180b9029914ff6d76e1766088ec55e7dd73", "parents": ["3fde5ca866c7a6bc71b06fde4ddacf4137823422", "ea869706644d3b2354b2438c77671d6e43df5e99"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Paul Adenot \u003cpaul@paul.cx\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1308436 - Don't convert the curve duration from double to float in the EventInsertionHelper to avoid losing precision. r=karlt\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9vazrYi3J8C\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4097", "files": ["dom/media/webaudio/AudioParam.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c781bf4c49700cd63bed43f09a1845701be96502", "parents": ["2b7a5180b9029914ff6d76e1766088ec55e7dd73"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Paul Adenot \u003cpaul@paul.cx\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1308436 - Add a test case for a negative curve duration in audioparam-exceptional-values.html. r=karlt\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4098", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/webaudio/the-audio-api/the-audioparam-interface/audioparam-exceptional-values.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "08897a32ca0578a8bc14722824fe5d0f187936de", "parents": ["c781bf4c49700cd63bed43f09a1845701be96502"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Paul Adenot \u003cpaul@paul.cx\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1308436 - Rework the AudioParam event insertion algorithm to be spec compliant, and fix the exception types and values. r=karlt\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4099", "files": ["dom/bindings/Errors.msg", "dom/media/webaudio/AudioEventTimeline.h", "dom/media/webaudio/AudioParam.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0a729b75c155246473d1c00a9f5622e8e3607530", "parents": ["08897a32ca0578a8bc14722824fe5d0f187936de"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Paul Adenot \u003cpaul@paul.cx\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1308436 - Adjust the AudioParam processing algorithm to match the spec.  r=karlt\n\nRamps now take into account the end of the curve as a start value for their\nautomation.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D3792", "files": ["dom/media/webaudio/AudioEventTimeline.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9f2140bc66e3e454984d139dc185f2cf9fd0411d", "parents": ["0a729b75c155246473d1c00a9f5622e8e3607530"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Paul Adenot \u003cpaul@paul.cx\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1308436 - Fix typo in audioparam-setValueCurve-exceptions.html. r=karlt\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DDAUkkwdACv\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4101", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/webaudio/the-audio-api/the-audioparam-interface/audioparam-setValueCurve-exceptions.html"