1\nka -\u003e 29da6798213e\npt-PT -\u003e 8e0e0b8341fa", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ba88b355a01a73275de4d78aaaacbe3976ef2583", "parents": ["801c3f0ecf3a3aaca57963d4d2122380d0668425"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\ncs -\u003e 46b3fc592927\ncy -\u003e 950f1f4e6541\nfi -\u003e b083fbcb6b9b\nka -\u003e 9076c08698f5\nlij -\u003e f38ae5057963\npt-PT -\u003e 8e0e0b8341fa\nro -\u003e f4df0e3db0b8", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "23c10d166ca91919fd5bb8599d433a535e99e0cd", "parents": ["ba88b355a01a73275de4d78aaaacbe3976ef2583"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536336066, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "9769": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1488427 - AbortSignal::Unfollow() must be called when unlinked, r=smaug a=RyanVM", "files": ["dom/abort/AbortSignal.cpp", "dom/abort/AbortSignal.h", "dom/fetch/Fetch.cpp", "dom/fetch/FetchObserver.cpp", "dom/fetch/Request.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9b35b8441aa544d0f5f066750b64f30e67fabcde", "parents": ["23c10d166ca91919fd5bb8599d433a535e99e0cd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1488414 - Add a test for perspective function interpolation. r=hiro a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5030", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/web-animations/animation-model/animation-types/property-types.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "aa1a35103016a558a011b999c915ca55a5062385", "parents": ["9b35b8441aa544d0f5f066750b64f30e67fabcde"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gabriele Svelto \u003cgsvelto@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1476250 - Simplify HAL initialization and shutdown to reduce the chance of leaks and UAFs r=froydnj a=pascalc\n\nThis patch initializes some HAL components greedily so that we can get rid of\nlazy initializers within the code. Observers are still lazily initialized\nbecause they can be instanced within content processes but that doesn't always\nhappen and we don't want to pay the memory price for structures we don't use.\n\nShutdown is now happening at a fixed time for all HAL components save\nWakeLocks. This ensures that we don't destroy an object while still iterating\nover it, something that could happen before.\n\nFinally a workaround for a compiler limitation has been removed.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D3100", "files": ["hal/Hal.cpp", "hal/Hal.h", "hal/HalWakeLock.cpp", "hal/HalWakeLockInternal.h", "widget/android/nsAppShell.cpp", "widget/android/nsAppShell.h", "widget/cocoa/nsAppShell.mm", "widget/gtk/nsAppShell.cpp", "widget/windows/nsAppShell.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7296296be48395ff3fd0706364b72cec35b2774e", "parents": ["aa1a35103016a558a011b999c915ca55a5062385"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Conley \u003cmconley@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1480951 - Make SessionStore respect sessionStorage.clear(). r=mikedeboer a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5066", "files": ["browser/components/sessionstore/ContentSessionStore.jsm", "browser/components/sessionstore/TabStateCache.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "736735078dd5a335d6293bc2a206d13f6a09f901", "parents": ["7296296be48395ff3fd0706364b72cec35b2774e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Conley \u003cmconley@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1480951 - Regression test. r=mikedeboer a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5067", "files": ["browser/components/sessionstore/test/browser_sessionStorage.js", "browser/components/sessionstore/test/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "586d84ba47a6f937fd498d8a98d06ebd7b85a96f", "parents": ["736735078dd5a335d6293bc2a206d13f6a09f901"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Petru Lingurar \u003cpetru.lingurar@softvision.ro\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1488720 - [Android M+] improve themes.xml; r=jchen a=pascalc\n\nThe issue in this ticket was because of missing menuItemSecondaryActionBarStyle,\nproperty of the menu items shown in the SecondaryActionBar.\n\nThe GeckoAppBase style from values-v23/themes.xml contained the properties\ninitially defined in the general values/themes.xml.\nNow changed to contain the properties from the closest values-v21/themes.xml.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5031", "files": ["mobile/android/app/src/main/res/values-v23/themes.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "078e8bfee2d11d0cc2da265144488f6c68b261c0", "parents": ["586d84ba47a6f937fd498d8a98d06ebd7b85a96f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Chen \u003cnchen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1489250 - Don't send window changed event if a11y is off; r=eeejay a=RyanVM\n\nDon't send window changed event if a11y has been turned off in the mean\ntime.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5192", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/SessionAccessibility.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c18e69fdab0675fefaa9985e8d1caf40e220c9f9", "parents": ["078e8bfee2d11d0cc2da265144488f6c68b261c0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Rob Wu \u003crob@robwu.nl\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1315513 - Replace test_ext_alarms_replaces with reliable test r=aswan a=test-only\n\nThe original test_ext_alarms_replaces test was sensitive to system loads\nthat slowed down the execution of the test, resulting in intermittent\nfailures.\n\nThis new test tests the equivalent behavior (namely that calling\nbrowser.alarms.create replaces a previous alarm), without being\nsensitive to system load. This is achieved by creating a repeating alarm\nand immediately replacing this alarm with a one-shot alarm that runs\nlater than the original alarm.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4698", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_ext_alarms_replaces.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "559c26308a99e80bf191a1fed66b6c5929137990", "parents": ["c18e69fdab0675fefaa9985e8d1caf40e220c9f9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nico Grunbaum \u003cna-g@nostrum.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1479632 - Increase accecptable PLI threshold in WebRTC Stats mochitest r=mjf a=test-only\n\nIncreasing the threshold for 'sane' for the pliCount stat to account for mochi tests running on a burdened machine\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5116", "files": ["dom/media/tests/mochitest/test_peerConnection_stats.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d4a4d249c8e79b6fd5f9ad95122fe94acadca0f8", "parents": ["559c26308a99e80bf191a1fed66b6c5929137990"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1488584 - Fix OOM test assumptions about whether OOM was previously reported on the context r=nbp a=test-only", "files": ["js/src/builtin/TestingFunctions.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3157946d732e919a60052f6bc124b312c70be1a5", "parents": ["d4a4d249c8e79b6fd5f9ad95122fe94acadca0f8"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536343508, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "dvarga@mozilla.com"}, "9770": {"changesets": [{"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1488414 - Use decomposition to interpolate matched perspective transform operations. r=birtles a=pascalc\n\nLooks like this produces sensible results for interpolation with 0, though I'm\nnot really convinced about the results from, let's say, 1px to 2000px in the\nattached test-case, I would've expected a linear interpolation from that to go\nthrough normal length interpolation.\n\ncss-transforms-1 says:\n\n  \u003e Two transform functions with the same name and the same number of arguments\n  \u003e are interpolated numerically without a former conversion. The calculated\n  \u003e value will be of the same transform function type with the same number of\n  \u003e arguments.\n  \u003e\n  \u003e Special rules apply to \u003cmatrix()\u003e.\n\nWhich is what we do... I was going to file a spec issue but turns out that it's\nalready addressed in css-transforms-2:\n\n  https://drafts.csswg.org/css-transforms-2/#interpolation-of-transform-functions\n\nWhich says:\n\n  \u003e The transform functions \u003cmatrix()\u003e, matrix3d() and perspective() get\n  \u003e converted into 4x4 matrices first and interpolated as defined in section\n  \u003e Interpolation of Matrices afterwards.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4942", "files": ["servo/components/style/properties/helpers/animated_properties.mako.rs", "servo/components/style/values/computed/transform.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7f9b2799bcb3457a1da42c4057ffafcfb02e76cf", "parents": ["3157946d732e919a60052f6bc124b312c70be1a5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1484905 - Don't mark MGetFirstDollarIndex as movable. r=arai a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4879", "files": ["js/src/jit-test/tests/ion/bug1484905.js", "js/src/jit/MIR.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e43b9c1507d221650d7155607dec87b18752e5b5", "parents": ["7f9b2799bcb3457a1da42c4057ffafcfb02e76cf"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536345616, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "9771": {"changesets": [{"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1488333 - Enable some mochitests for editor which were disabled on debug build of Android due to bug 1480702 r=m_kato a=test-only\n\nBecause of the rewrite of test_request.html, now, we can enable the mochitests\nfor editor which were disabled on debug build of Android due to bug 1480702.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4904", "files": ["editor/libeditor/tests/mochitest.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "270504f95e5846c9e0de365bf039be992bfdf4d8", "parents": ["e43b9c1507d221650d7155607dec87b18752e5b5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Geoffrey Sneddon \u003cme@gsnedders.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1472172: Re-disable old css-transitions tests. r=gsnedders a=test-only\nThe meta file in css-transitions-1 should've been, but wasn't, moved\nin bug 1419296, causing these tests to be re-enabled. This re-disables\nonly the tests using the old, flaky harness. r=jgraham , r=birtles\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 43Bp4P5VB5t", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-transitions/before-DOMContentLoaded-001.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-transitions/before-load-001.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-transitions/changing-while-transition.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-transitions/detached-container-001.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-transitions/hidden-container-001.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-transitions/properties-value-001.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-transitions/properties-value-002.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-transitions/properties-value-003.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-transitions/properties-value-auto-001.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-transitions/properties-value-implicit-001.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-transitions/properties-value-inherit-001.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-transitions/properties-value-inherit-002.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-transitions/properties-value-inherit-003.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/css/css-transitions/pseudo-elements-001.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "17abec48413689466014a2cafc7e2dc68f1f6732", "parents": ["270504f95e5846c9e0de365bf039be992bfdf4d8"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536347061, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ncsoregi@mozilla.com"}, "9772": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nit -\u003e acb2c21f0ca4", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a3c9db6957bde0a0b6ffc39c817d0e00215430ab", "parents": ["17abec48413689466014a2cafc7e2dc68f1f6732"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536411627, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "9773": {"changesets": [{"author": "Petru Lingurar \u003cpetru.lingurar@softvision.ro\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1480083 - After exiting PIP the restarted activity should have device's orientation; r=sdaswani a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4939", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/BrowserApp.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "093d1a92ce0856127a2b49039a9a4e07f5e147ed", "parents": ["a3c9db6957bde0a0b6ffc39c817d0e00215430ab"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sylvestre Ledru \u003csledru@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1486759 - Cherry pick a lld fix to fix the Windows entry point r=dmajor a=pascalc\n\nNot waiting for rc3 or final from llvm because the issue is pretty severe\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5124", "files": ["build/build-clang/clang-win64.json", "build/build-clang/r341035.patch"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "151237fbc3d264f61db1b1f289bc635050e72b91", "parents": ["093d1a92ce0856127a2b49039a9a4e07f5e147ed"], "tags": []}, {"author": "\u5f35\u4fca\u829d \u003czjz@zjz.name\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1485581 - Make nsImageFrame report intrinsic inline sizes in the correct dimension (height) when writing-mode is vertical.  r=dbaron a=pascalc", "files": ["layout/generic/nsFrame.h", "layout/generic/nsImageFrame.cpp", "testing/web-platform/meta/MANIFEST.json", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-writing-modes/img-intrinsic-size-contribution-001.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-writing-modes/img-intrinsic-size-contribution-002.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-writing-modes/img-intrinsic-size-contribution-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-writing-modes/support/blue-200x100.png"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8614b6f4970aad89d9748a36223f27408ef16047", "parents": ["151237fbc3d264f61db1b1f289bc635050e72b91"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Francois Marier \u003cfrancois@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1489590 - Teach the URL classifier about the FastBlock lists. r=dimi a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5297", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f7a8a2d68c01f5e71f6051406240766e9542f1da", "parents": ["8614b6f4970aad89d9748a36223f27408ef16047"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1488448 - Ignore case on blacklist check. r=adw a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4950", "files": ["toolkit/components/search/nsSearchService.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/test_blacklist.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7b56a5ad6f1f5a1a8db08e5a27b8cc947ea18db6", "parents": ["f7a8a2d68c01f5e71f6051406240766e9542f1da"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Odvarko \u003codvarko@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1487274 - Use nsIHttpChannel.isThirdPartyTrackingResource to identify trackers; r=nchevobbe a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5018", "files": ["devtools/client/netmonitor/src/components/RequestListColumnDomain.js", "devtools/client/netmonitor/src/connector/firefox-data-provider.js", "devtools/client/netmonitor/src/constants.js", "devtools/client/netmonitor/test/browser_net_tracking-resources.js", "devtools/client/netmonitor/test/html_tracking-protection.html", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/fixtures/stubs/networkEvent.js", "devtools/server/actors/network-event.js", "devtools/server/actors/network-monitor/network-observer.js", "devtools/shared/webconsole/client.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1deae1b8cd1d08c21c3c42a541dcebc9d909f200", "parents": ["7b56a5ad6f1f5a1a8db08e5a27b8cc947ea18db6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Botond Ballo \u003cbotond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1482825 - Only prevent dispatching mouse-move events targeted at a slider frame to web content, if the scrollbar is being dragged. r=smaug a=pascalc\n\nOtherwise, if the mouse is just moving over the scrollbar, mouse-move\nevents are dispatched to web content.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4800", "files": ["layout/xul/nsSliderFrame.cpp", "layout/xul/nsSliderFrame.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f296b260e6112bee24ab32a9a9e393ef423f9754", "parents": ["1deae1b8cd1d08c21c3c42a541dcebc9d909f200"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Neil Deakin \u003cneil@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1484176, somewhat revert the change from bug 1454358 for places menu.xml since the boxObject being used should be for the inner scrollbox, r=dao a=pascalc", "files": ["browser/components/places/content/menu.xml", "toolkit/content/widgets/scrollbox.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a11b319df87e39805148cfe7a00099a6b073a366", "parents": ["f296b260e6112bee24ab32a9a9e393ef423f9754"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536579504, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "dvarga@mozilla.com"}, "9774": {"changesets": [{"author": "Johan Lorenzo \u003cjlorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1489132 - Ensure geckoview build numbers are always MAJOR.MINOR.BUILDID r=sebastian,jchen a=release\n\nSummary: Ensure geckoview build numbers are always MAJOR.MINOR.BUILDID\n\nTest Plan: https://tools.taskcluster.net/groups/GO4L4WxkTTiwlF-OvPRsrQ/tasks/MK0jdBw8QRmcLM-MbUROIg/runs/0/logs/public%2Flogs%2Flive_backing.log#L1770 Even though MOZ_APP_VERSION is 64.0.1, maven version is 64.0.20180907165027\n\nReviewers: sebastian, jchen\n\nTags: #secure-revision\n\nBug #: 1489132\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5290", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/build.gradle"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e654bee36498bb850cac4f7418ad14f8e68043cc", "parents": ["a11b319df87e39805148cfe7a00099a6b073a366"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536581092, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "jlorenzo@mozilla.com"}, "9775": {"changesets": [{"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1398111 - [marionette] Update mainFrame and curFrame when switching chrome windows. r=ato a=test-only\n\nWhen switching between chrome windows Marionette doesn't update\nits references for the mainFrame (current chrome window) and\ncurFrame (current frame inside the chrome window). Instead it\ngets currently only updated when a new chrome window opens.\n\nIt means that in most cases Marionette sets the focus on the\nwrong chrome window and frame.", "files": ["testing/marionette/driver.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e511024df8706eec5cc0ad7d7abf3d12d07ca2a1", "parents": ["e654bee36498bb850cac4f7418ad14f8e68043cc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1398111 - [marionette] Virtually set Firefox as top-most application in WebDriver:NewSession. r=ato a=test-only\n\nTo allow the focusmanager testmode to raise focus events even with\nthe Firefox window in the background, the current chrome window has\nto be virtually brought into foreground. This should be at least\nalways done when creating a new session.", "files": ["testing/marionette/driver.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0b67c71093360c70ae5a66673ef07cdf8bddcec7", "parents": ["e511024df8706eec5cc0ad7d7abf3d12d07ca2a1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1398111 - [marionette] Never disable focus manager test mode for unit tests. r=ato a=test-only\n\nWith the fix on bug 1334981 the focus manager test mode has\nno longer to be disabled for the unit tests.", "files": ["testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_switch_window_chrome.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "08f205f8d6aaa9c39173f392b0547b696677306a", "parents": ["0b67c71093360c70ae5a66673ef07cdf8bddcec7"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536582464, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "ebalazs@mozilla.com"}, "9776": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003cffxbld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug, mozilla-beta repo-update HSTS HPKP remote-settings - a=repo-update r=mtabara\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5412", "files": ["security/manager/ssl/StaticHPKPins.h", "security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.inc"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8477f35bdf65c1e9aef50704420bfecf2a471924", "parents": ["08f205f8d6aaa9c39173f392b0547b696677306a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Marco Bonardo \u003cmbonardo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1482494 - Intermittent failure in browser_urlbarSearchFunction.js. r=adw, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5144", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/urlbar/browser.ini", "browser/base/content/test/urlbar/browser_urlbarSearchFunction.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2e81606ad203f544ad43579e57e4247ec8453ab7", "parents": ["8477f35bdf65c1e9aef50704420bfecf2a471924"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1488412 - Make sure we wait for the right loads in browser_privatebrowsing_concurrent.js. r=mconley, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5173", "files": ["browser/components/privatebrowsing/test/browser/browser_privatebrowsing_concurrent.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "69daa09be6b7b325dd099f3080020910cb2964e3", "parents": ["2e81606ad203f544ad43579e57e4247ec8453ab7"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536584944, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "9777": {"changesets": [{"author": "Petru Lingurar \u003cpetru.lingurar@softvision.ro\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1488691 - Prevent registering listeners if PIP failed; r=jchen a=pascalc\n\nAlso, if entering PIP fails will make sure that upon restarting the activity\nit's orientation will match device's.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5035", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/BrowserApp.java", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/media/PictureInPictureController.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "554953db0c6120f7c67794dfb1bd5b493f15749d", "parents": ["69daa09be6b7b325dd099f3080020910cb2964e3"], "tags": ["DEVEDITION_63_0b5_BUILD1", "DEVEDITION_63_0b5_RELEASE", "FENNEC_63_0b5_BUILD1", "FENNEC_63_0b5_RELEASE", "FIREFOX_63_0b5_BUILD1", "FIREFOX_63_0b5_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1536585856, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "9778": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 554953db0c6120f7c67794dfb1bd5b493f15749d with FENNEC_63_0b5_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b0456d21ba3ebd26912ddfce555cc75f150ab9cf", "parents": ["554953db0c6120f7c67794dfb1bd5b493f15749d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536591216, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "9779": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 554953db0c6120f7c67794dfb1bd5b493f15749d with FIREFOX_63_0b5_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "39d0d1dd3123aadade78eb1639455692a8b31303", "parents": ["b0456d21ba3ebd26912ddfce555cc75f150ab9cf"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536591392, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "9780": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 554953db0c6120f7c67794dfb1bd5b493f15749d with DEVEDITION_63_0b5_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b36d5eeb2745d7a664824678bf3527b0de6ef62f", "parents": ["39d0d1dd3123aadade78eb1639455692a8b31303"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536591565, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "9781": {"changesets": [{"author": "Tim Nguyen \u003cntim.bugs@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1489495 - Fix synced tabs sidebar instructions text color with WebExtension themes. r=dao a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5257", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/syncedtabs/sidebar.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "37a14b8986b453da423466235d2bf7798c8e7da2", "parents": ["b36d5eeb2745d7a664824678bf3527b0de6ef62f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Drew Willcoxon \u003cadw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1488879 - Autofill non-hidden origins and URLs with frecencies \u003c= 0. r=mak a=pascalc\n\n(1) Modify the threshold calculation so the minimum threshold is 0, not 1.  That means that no moz_origins will be excluded from consideration because their frecencies are 0.  moz_origins always have frecencies \u003e= 0.\n\n(2) Modify the urlQuery to include moz_places with -1 frecencies but that aren't hidden.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5308", "files": ["toolkit/components/places/UnifiedComplete.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/unifiedcomplete/autofill_tasks.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/unifiedcomplete/test_zero_frecency.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/unifiedcomplete/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7c59422b8e3cb6c7c58461fc83d62c2e8f534fa1", "parents": ["37a14b8986b453da423466235d2bf7798c8e7da2"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536666713, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ebalazs@mozilla.com"}, "9782": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 554953db0c6120f7c67794dfb1bd5b493f15749d with FIREFOX_63_0b5_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "081b016461f0e0fb7fa207d8e9e9cfa5557cc8c4", "parents": ["7c59422b8e3cb6c7c58461fc83d62c2e8f534fa1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Automatic version bump CLOSED TREE NO BUG a=release", "files": ["browser/config/version_display.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "64cbeda859d7704a61522043ee7563c2780b2509", "parents": ["081b016461f0e0fb7fa207d8e9e9cfa5557cc8c4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536679482, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "9783": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 554953db0c6120f7c67794dfb1bd5b493f15749d with DEVEDITION_63_0b5_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0401cbd49102a54758da1e7481a4c4cede43aa2d", "parents": ["64cbeda859d7704a61522043ee7563c2780b2509"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536679670, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "9784": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 554953db0c6120f7c67794dfb1bd5b493f15749d with FENNEC_63_0b5_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "07483c8ccaecffbd0973589576cf9759bd61eb59", "parents": ["0401cbd49102a54758da1e7481a4c4cede43aa2d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536680717, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "9785": {"changesets": [{"author": "Michael Cooper \u003cmcooper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1488927 - Make about:studies \"remove\" button work again. r=aswan a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5089", "files": ["toolkit/components/normandy/content/AboutPages.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d9fa17a67b48cc270c40bb451077f5c8b6b21e9b", "parents": ["07483c8ccaecffbd0973589576cf9759bd61eb59"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536690413, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "nbeleuzu@mozilla.com"}, "9786": {"changesets": [{"author": "Nicholas Nethercote \u003cnnethercote@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1489744 - Fix a bounds violation crash in the prefs parser. r=glandium a=RyanVM\n\nCurrently, if a get_char() call returns EOF, the index moves beyond the\nbuffer's bounds and get_char() cannot be called again without triggering a\npanic. As a result, everywhere that encounters an EOF and then does subsequent\nparsing ungets the EOF... except there was one place that failed to do that:\nthe match case for CharKind::Slash in get_token(). This meant that a single '/'\nat the end of the input could trigger a bounds violation (but only if it is the\nstart of a new token).\n\nThis EOF-unget requirement is subtle and easy to get wrong, so this patch\neliminates it. get_char() now can be called repeatedly after an EOF, and will\nreturn EOF on each subsequent call. This means that some of the existing\nunget_char() calls can be removed. Some others are still necessary to get line\nnumbers correct in error messages, but the outcome of mishandled cases is now\nmuch less drastic -- an incorrect line number in an error message instead of a\npanic.\n\nThe patch also clarifies a couple of related comments.", "files": ["modules/libpref/parser/src/lib.rs", "modules/libpref/test/gtest/Parser.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2676e53112584b2c08b9a1bf02e15cd9bb0d0ee5", "parents": ["d9fa17a67b48cc270c40bb451077f5c8b6b21e9b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536690632, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "nbeleuzu@mozilla.com"}, "9787": {"changesets": [{"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1489820 - Don't handle locale changes on shutdown. r=gandalf a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5466", "files": ["toolkit/components/search/nsSearchService.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "992b31153c1fb7d096902f6ed47b646a422d3c9c", "parents": ["2676e53112584b2c08b9a1bf02e15cd9bb0d0ee5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536690752, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "nbeleuzu@mozilla.com"}, "9788": {"changesets": [{"author": "Landry Breuil \u003clandry@openbsd.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1466593 - When sandboxing the content process on OpenBSD, fake a DBUS session if none is running r=gcp a=pascalc", "files": ["dom/ipc/ContentChild.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cae2f8c62a2a2231d93f3ddc02f19f34d33739a5", "parents": ["992b31153c1fb7d096902f6ed47b646a422d3c9c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daniel Holbert \u003cdholbert@cs.stanford.edu\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1486086: Switch to use logical axes, for stale physical-axis-based flex-item border/padding calculation. r=mats a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4974", "files": ["layout/generic/nsFlexContainerFrame.cpp", "layout/reftests/w3c-css/submitted/flexbox/flexbox-writing-mode-016-ref.html", "layout/reftests/w3c-css/submitted/flexbox/flexbox-writing-mode-016.html", "layout/reftests/w3c-css/submitted/flexbox/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "90b715327727c8b565e5d4019f62bd14bc742c7c", "parents": ["cae2f8c62a2a2231d93f3ddc02f19f34d33739a5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Martin Stransky \u003cstransky@redhat.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1487763 - [Wayland] Set scale factor settings before wl_surface commit, r=jhorak a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5029", "files": ["widget/gtk/WindowSurfaceWayland.cpp", "widget/gtk/WindowSurfaceWayland.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "07f61c345475ce279808a26bee71636216ede6b2", "parents": ["90b715327727c8b565e5d4019f62bd14bc742c7c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Chen \u003cnchen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1489569 - 1. Avoid unnecessary setActive calls; r=droeh a=pascalc\n\nTo avoid unnecessary setActive calls, only call it when we have a\ndisplay and when the display acquires or releases a surface. In other\ncases, we can delay the setActive call until later.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5328", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/GeckoView.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3c3062f20a3d9c69655dd8c85a7a28ffd97bc7ff", "parents": ["07f61c345475ce279808a26bee71636216ede6b2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Chen \u003cnchen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1489569 - 2. Don't blur window on temporary focus loss; r=droeh a=pascalc\n\nWhen the window temporarily loses focus (e.g. due to auto-fill popups),\ndon't call setFocus(false). Otherwise, we can end up disrupting user\ninteraction (e.g. causing the auto-fill popup to flicker). Only call\nsetFocus(false) when we are reasonably sure the focus loss is not\ntemporary.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5329", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/GeckoView.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c38cf879410f5d90b7d87f2e13f108f5c9b3d133", "parents": ["3c3062f20a3d9c69655dd8c85a7a28ffd97bc7ff"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536752237, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ebalazs@mozilla.com"}, "9789": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mihai Tabara \u003cmtabara@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1475101 - add mark-as-started task. r=rail a=release", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/release-mark-as-started/kind.yml", "taskcluster/docs/kinds.rst", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/release_mark_as_started.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/task.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/util/scriptworker.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "950b4168885978e03fba79c983a007ade5e50ae9", "parents": ["c38cf879410f5d90b7d87f2e13f108f5c9b3d133"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536757150, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "raliiev@mozilla.com"}, "9790": {"changesets": [{"author": "Julien Cristau \u003cjcristau@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug: Turn off staged rollout for Fennec 63.0b.  a=release DONTBUILD", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/push-apk/kind.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5aceea1124f9a56489368152dc6c3e17d8a1dae4", "parents": ["950b4168885978e03fba79c983a007ade5e50ae9"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536757355, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "jcristau@mozilla.com"}, "9791": {"changesets": [{"author": "Cameron McCormack \u003ccam@mcc.id.au\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1477079 - Skip XBL style building if document's pres shell went away. r=emilio a=pascalc", "files": ["dom/xbl/nsXBLResourceLoader.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1ff507e1820103ce83ec6e1d44915c1dc1ed0071", "parents": ["5aceea1124f9a56489368152dc6c3e17d8a1dae4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1488934. Handle unpacked to packed migration. r=kmag a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5565", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/internal/XPIProvider.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8bc16d134d87cf5b1289b4de0ba6b9132a1b17fb", "parents": ["1ff507e1820103ce83ec6e1d44915c1dc1ed0071"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536769493, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ncsoregi@mozilla.com"}, "9792": {"changesets": [{"author": "Botond Ballo \u003cbotond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1478335 - Use the visual viewport offset to compute the visible area in CalculateRectToZoomTo(). r=kats a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5462", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/util/DoubleTapToZoom.cpp", "layout/base/nsLayoutUtils.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c22ce582889030dfca1885db8a9f9e0ca82e26c5", "parents": ["8bc16d134d87cf5b1289b4de0ba6b9132a1b17fb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Francois Marier \u003cfrancois@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1488951 - Put a limit on how long FastBlock runs. r=mayhemer,Ehsan a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5098", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/trackingUI/browser_trackingUI_state.js", "modules/libpref/init/all.js", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpChannel.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dbf69e2a3a0e5639b329cdfd090c7373b44e0b6d", "parents": ["c22ce582889030dfca1885db8a9f9e0ca82e26c5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Yura Zenevich \u003cyura.zenevich@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1490776 - fix noGrip array rendering in a11y panel sidebar. r=gl a=pascalc\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4QAPbUBYiCW\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5697", "files": ["devtools/client/accessibility/components/Accessible.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "263df0c4e8e4da73e23e9fc7bec8b06a16de15be", "parents": ["dbf69e2a3a0e5639b329cdfd090c7373b44e0b6d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1489141 - [webdriver] Ignore any unknown variant of enum PointerOrigin. r=ato a=test-only\n\nTo keep backward compatibility, the legacy \"ELEMENT\" key for an\ninstance of PointerOrigin has to be supported, but ignored.\n\nThis workaround can be removed once legacy support gets dropped\nfrom geckodriver.", "files": ["testing/webdriver/src/actions.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "39b50c15dc4d47d64f2e3bd0ca96f3801228e6cf", "parents": ["263df0c4e8e4da73e23e9fc7bec8b06a16de15be"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536827813, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ebalazs@mozilla.com"}, "9793": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003cffxbld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug, mozilla-beta repo-update HSTS HPKP blocklist remote-settings - a=repo-update r=mtabara\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5759", "files": ["browser/app/blocklist.xml", "security/manager/ssl/StaticHPKPins.h", "security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.inc", "services/settings/dumps/blocklists/plugins.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "76ea80f9f4414e4619581bcd611010e8af3adc65", "parents": ["39b50c15dc4d47d64f2e3bd0ca96f3801228e6cf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1392106 - Annotate more failing tests as random on Win7. r=jmaher, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5688", "files": ["layout/reftests/bidi/dirAuto/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/bidi/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/bugs/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/font-face/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/font-features/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/font-inflation/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/forms/legend/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/mathml/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/svg/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/svg/text/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/text/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/w3c-css/failures.list", "layout/reftests/w3c-css/received/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/w3c-css/submitted/counter-styles-3/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/w3c-css/submitted/flexbox/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/w3c-css/submitted/text-decor-3/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/w3c-css/submitted/writing-modes-3/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/webkit-box/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/writing-mode/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "291d7a2a5bea36e16bf8c2958fb518c90e1bc49d", "parents": ["76ea80f9f4414e4619581bcd611010e8af3adc65"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1475907 - Skip element-paint-transform-repeated.html on Win7 for repeated intermittent failures. r=me, a=test-only", "files": ["layout/reftests/image-element/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e3940284637654d919864ec515fb13f0323fe714", "parents": ["291d7a2a5bea36e16bf8c2958fb518c90e1bc49d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1438402 - Fix intermittent browser_csp_block_all_mixedcontent.js. r=nhnt11, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5406", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/siteIdentity/browser.ini", "browser/base/content/test/siteIdentity/browser_csp_block_all_mixedcontent.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2dec8bceca0197876e3c12b34682d8a0c1df8584", "parents": ["e3940284637654d919864ec515fb13f0323fe714"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1376771 - Fix intermittent browser_mcb_redirect.js. r=nhnt11, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5270", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/siteIdentity/browser.ini", "browser/base/content/test/siteIdentity/browser_mcb_redirect.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b021e40c789070407416751f1c5fae51928971b6", "parents": ["2dec8bceca0197876e3c12b34682d8a0c1df8584"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1489287 - Always try to eagerly-place a floating first-letter frame. r=mats, a=RyanVM\n\nTo avoid its deferred reflow potentially killing continuations that are parented\nto the parent of the letter frame.\n\nThis rolls back to the behavior previous to bug 488725 just for this case, until\nwe fix it properly in bug 1490281. This also fixes bug 1489863.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5521", "files": ["layout/generic/crashtests/1489287.html", "layout/generic/crashtests/crashtests.list", "layout/generic/nsLineLayout.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c304540f5b9881242c1b9b9664b84353b3a3ca02", "parents": ["b021e40c789070407416751f1c5fae51928971b6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1489863 - Add a crashtest. r=dholbert, a=test-only\n\nThis crashtest is simpler than the one from bug 1489287, so I think we should\nland it.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5523", "files": ["layout/generic/crashtests/1489863.html", "layout/generic/crashtests/crashtests.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "aa25b33273dd8308389cb27362b0f4158fdad0ce", "parents": ["c304540f5b9881242c1b9b9664b84353b3a3ca02"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536843780, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "9794": {"changesets": [{"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1469400 - Add additional codes to blacklist. r=mikedeboer a=pascalc", "files": ["toolkit/components/search/nsSearchService.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b9d0f86adcd418361d58938427128a95fecea7e4", "parents": ["aa25b33273dd8308389cb27362b0f4158fdad0ce"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Drew Willcoxon \u003cadw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1484737 - Improve the handling of search alias highlighting in the urlbar. r=Mardak,mak a=pascalc\n\nThis has two parts:\n\n(1) urlbar already had a formatValue method. Right now, it only does the URL formatting (domain highlighting, crossing out https for mixed content pages) that we do when the urlbar is not focused. This patch generalizes that method into a kind of \"any formatting you want to do, do it here\" method, and it adds alias formatting.\n\nformatValue is called by the base autocomplete binding when `value` is set. So it's called when the selection in the popup changes and the autocomplete controller subsequently sets the input value. (It's also called by urlbar on focus and blur.) And if anyone else sets the value directly, it'll be called then too of course.\n\nBut it's not called when you're just typing in the input, so I added a call in urlbar.onResultsAdded, where we were calling highlightSearchAlias, to handle the first heuristic result being added or modified as a result of what you type.\n\nSo I think that should cover all possible times we need to highlight the alias?\n\n(2) Just looking at the selected result to get the alias in the input doesn't work all the time. If you click a search tile on newtab and then key around in the popup, sometimes when you key down to the one-off buttons, the input value reverts to the alias (it's the user-typed value I guess?), but at the time that the value setter is called during the revert, the popup's selected index is still the last selection in the popup. IOW the selected index doesn't match up with what's in the input.\n\nRather than deal with that, it seems safer to call PlacesSearchAutocompleteProvider.findMatchByAlias() on the first word in the input. But that has a couple of problems. It's async, and I noticed there can be a slight delay in the highlighting appearing. Also, we've already gotten the information returned by that method, when we generated the results in the first place, so it seems inelegant to call it again.\n\nSo what I've done instead is to cache aliases in the popup when results are added, and then just look up the first word in the input in these aliases. We shouldn't reset this cache until the first result of a new search comes in.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D3850", "files": ["browser/base/content/urlbarBindings.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c365b95955141b6336da5656e4406186e457ddb1", "parents": ["b9d0f86adcd418361d58938427128a95fecea7e4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Florian Qu\u00e8ze \u003cflorian@queze.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1489852 - convert the size from outer to inner window dimensions when setting the width and height to use when the user leaves the maximized mode, r=mconley. a=pascalc", "files": ["browser/components/nsBrowserGlue.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0daf051f7fc7c5fc5c9dacb33f4d1b49e755c952", "parents": ["c365b95955141b6336da5656e4406186e457ddb1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Florian Qu\u00e8ze \u003cflorian@queze.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1489214 - Set the position of the early blank window with the screenX/Y attributes rather than with the left/top features to avoid broken CSS \u003c-\u003e device pixel conversions in mixed DPI environments, r=mconley. a=pascalc", "files": ["browser/components/nsBrowserGlue.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c954d9ac0d5cc4bc4fb9c40f34e1ba5deb3ef79c", "parents": ["0daf051f7fc7c5fc5c9dacb33f4d1b49e755c952"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Henning \u003cjh+bugzilla@buttercookie.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1489594 - Decouple application-background event from clearing of current activity. r=jchen a=pascalc\n\nWhen the OS needs to display a permission prompt, our current activity is paused\nand onSaveInstanceState gets called, however the activity isn't stopped yet.\nWhen the permission handling then returns with the results to us, we display\nthe file picker using the current activity as retrieved from the GeckoActivity-\nMonitor.\n\nThe problem is that in bug 1437382, our application-background handling was\nchanged such that it would already be triggered by the preparatory onSave-\nInstanceState call. This had the side effect that the current activity would\nbe cleared from the GeckoActivityMonitor at that point already. Therefore, in\nour case showing the file picker would fail because the GAM would have cleared\nthe current activity already after the runtime permission prompt caused our\nprevious activity to save its state.\n\nTo fix this, we change the behaviour of the GeckoActivityMonitor such that it\nwill continue to trigger our application-background handling during onSave-\nInstanceState if possible, but will only clear the current activity when it is\nstopping for real.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5304", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/GeckoActivityMonitor.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9114c6ecda72724ed8a763bb61991347f3f3ad10", "parents": ["c954d9ac0d5cc4bc4fb9c40f34e1ba5deb3ef79c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1487419 - Save current desktop configuration in ScreenCapturerMac::Init; r=pehrsons a=pascalc\n\nSummary:\nThe fix for Bug 1409018 accidentally removed saving the current desktop\nconfiguration during Init() which causes it to not be set when a different\nscreen is selected, meaning that regardless of the choice made, only the\nfirst screen is captured.\n\nReviewers: pehrsons\n\nTags: #secure-revision\n\nBug #: 1487419\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5062", "files": ["media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/desktop_capture/screen_capturer_mac.mm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "feca63da8d4fc91c004f17c9ca88a8d2d7fc3cd9", "parents": ["9114c6ecda72724ed8a763bb61991347f3f3ad10"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Shane Caraveo \u003cscaraveo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1488055 fix loading ext-browser-content script in sidebar when browser_style=false, r=rpl a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5196", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.js", "browser/base/content/webext-panels.js", "browser/components/extensions/test/browser/browser-common.ini", "browser/components/extensions/test/browser/browser_ext_sidebarAction_click.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "47094cecc7e14e43940958bc3e4a03fb9e0cfaf7", "parents": ["feca63da8d4fc91c004f17c9ca88a8d2d7fc3cd9"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536846470, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "apavel@mozilla.com"}, "9795": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kershaw Chang \u003ckershaw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1487085 - Allow to set cookie with a null channel in child process, r=valentin a=pascalc\n\nIn the current implmentation of CookieServiceChild::SetCookieString, pass a null channel will crash the child process. This is because we call aChannel-\u003eGetURI() without checking if aChannel is null.\nHowever, set cookie with a null channel is possible in non-e10s mode. To make sure the behavior to be consistent in both non-e10s and e10s mode, we have to pass an empty URIParams in child process.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5432", "files": ["netwerk/cookie/CookieServiceChild.cpp", "netwerk/cookie/CookieServiceParent.cpp", "netwerk/cookie/CookieServiceParent.h", "netwerk/cookie/PCookieService.ipdl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "44b8aa9ccb46f8e6ee59a7fadf2011961d209b88", "parents": ["47094cecc7e14e43940958bc3e4a03fb9e0cfaf7"], "tags": ["DEVEDITION_63_0b6_BUILD1", "DEVEDITION_63_0b6_RELEASE", "FIREFOX_63_0b6_BUILD1", "FIREFOX_63_0b6_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1536848075, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "apavel@mozilla.com"}, "9796": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 44b8aa9ccb46f8e6ee59a7fadf2011961d209b88 with DEVEDITION_63_0b6_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f0fc3f747808a015ec3874da3c2c766a3e74da52", "parents": ["44b8aa9ccb46f8e6ee59a7fadf2011961d209b88"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536859434, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "9797": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 44b8aa9ccb46f8e6ee59a7fadf2011961d209b88 with FIREFOX_63_0b6_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a172f86636c74b09c76b1de937345e5a1db040f3", "parents": ["f0fc3f747808a015ec3874da3c2c766a3e74da52"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536859796, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "9798": {"changesets": [{"author": "Dylan Roeh \u003cdroeh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1489257 - Backed out 3 changesets (bug 1441059, bug 1478171) for causing bug 1489257. r=me a=RyanVM\n\nBacked out changeset f7bd4f224f9a (bug 1441059)\nBacked out changeset e66e6bd82e3f (bug 1441059)\nBacked out changeset 94cfd6113ca7 (bug 1478171)", "files": ["docshell/base/nsDocShell.cpp", "docshell/base/nsIDocShell.idl", "mfbt/Maybe.h", "mobile/android/chrome/geckoview/GeckoViewNavigationContent.js", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/androidTest/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/test/NavigationDelegateTest.kt", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/androidTest/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/test/ProgressDelegateTest.kt", "mobile/android/modules/geckoview/GeckoViewNavigation.jsm", "mobile/android/modules/geckoview/LoadURIDelegate.jsm", "netwerk/base/nsIChannelEventSink.idl", "uriloader/base/nsDocLoader.cpp", "xpcom/base/nsILoadURIDelegate.idl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fedb26132f9a4b3ff3ccbe0762f38db40c8c9cce", "parents": ["a172f86636c74b09c76b1de937345e5a1db040f3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536940153, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "droeh@mozilla.com"}, "9799": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 44b8aa9ccb46f8e6ee59a7fadf2011961d209b88 with DEVEDITION_63_0b6_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2d5c2b359077d3946c873a0f5af9d86ab3a67d39", "parents": ["fedb26132f9a4b3ff3ccbe0762f38db40c8c9cce"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Automatic version bump CLOSED TREE NO BUG a=release", "files": ["browser/config/version_display.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fc56f636db011b20634d92c2fc08ab492d06b985", "parents": ["2d5c2b359077d3946c873a0f5af9d86ab3a67d39"], "tags": []}], "date": 1536940897, "git_changesets": [null, null