: "Bug 1484829: Handle arbitrary absolute links for the TZ environment variable. r=Waldo a=pascalc", "files": ["js/src/vm/DateTime.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c83151139ae0621aedb4aecb313096b66d493d0a", "parents": ["19165f791f18c6373dfd95377a41e4f2599ca224"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jean-Yves Avenard \u003cjyavenard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1491132 - Clamp cache reads to content size. r=gerald a=pascalc\n\nPrior bug 1416085, reads were clamped to the content's duration (if known). It appears that the new code relied on MediaCacheReadBlockFromCache to properly account for the end of content.\n\nHowever, this was not the case, the MediaCache always reads (and write) one full block at a time regardles of the size requested (a block is 32768 bytes).\n\nRather than clamping in the Read() method as it used to be, we clamp in ReadBlockFromCache as such safety will benefit other callers that would have otherwise also returned garbage reads.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5964", "files": ["dom/media/MediaCache.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "65192994f66b995fac39f2c1c159e441d28e230b", "parents": ["c83151139ae0621aedb4aecb313096b66d493d0a"], "tags": []}], "date": 1537298717, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "apavel@mozilla.com"}, "9831": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nbe -\u003e 3d60d7d735a8\ncy -\u003e 8be81b467ef4\nnl -\u003e 8bc00cedecfe\nsv-SE -\u003e af09998ea41b\nzh-CN -\u003e 8472190fbaed", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8514768ede9e438832bce21b552d0af548a35e0b", "parents": ["65192994f66b995fac39f2c1c159e441d28e230b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nar -\u003e c244c59ff613\nbe -\u003e 3d60d7d735a8\ncy -\u003e 8be81b467ef4\ndsb -\u003e b57bb9412b77\nen-CA -\u003e b6020194a5e8\nfr -\u003e a0b956786512\ngu-IN -\u003e c83849bdc055\nhsb -\u003e 712557313425\nnl -\u003e 8bc00cedecfe\nsv-SE -\u003e af09998ea41b\nzh-CN -\u003e 8472190fbaed", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5cdd1306720d9c0561605a8ce30a49a78d6debe4", "parents": ["8514768ede9e438832bce21b552d0af548a35e0b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1537300834, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "9832": {"changesets": [{"author": "Rob Lemley \u003crob@thunderbird.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1489355 - Windows installer build fixes r=Callek a=tomprince\n\nBug 1484264 made changes to how the repackage tasks is configured.\nThe package-name field was hard-coded to \"firefox\". This field is later\nused to build the Windows installer, and Thunderbird requires that it\nbe set to \"thunderbird\" or the build fails.\n\nThis patch changes package-name to be a templated field like the others.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5222", "files": ["taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/repackage.py", "testing/mozharness/configs/repackage/base.py", "testing/mozharness/scripts/repackage.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fc74c45b068165e42fddb62fb7b13ed34f14b1b8", "parents": ["5cdd1306720d9c0561605a8ce30a49a78d6debe4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1537302188, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "mozilla@jorgk.com"}, "9833": {"changesets": [{"author": "Makoto Kato \u003cm_kato@ga2.so-net.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1488803 - Don't allocate PendingAction twice. r=masayuki, a=pascalc", "files": ["widget/windows/TSFTextStore.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2437048d2297874f10cdf6476e0c2761a5ba311b", "parents": ["fc7